<h2 id="510">4. Carrying out the group function</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the group function to send an email template, print address label or add a contact to a newsletter folder. This can be done simultaneously for one or multiple contacts.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Carrying out the group function:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Group function</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate one or multiple procedures and select the options from the drop-down menus. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-contact-group-function">Table 4</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the contact(s) that you would like to carry out the procedure for.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Group function</strong> to carry out the selected procedures for the activated contacts.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
