<h2 id="1800">11. Displaying the account balance</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Account</strong> view lists the revenues of your contacts. In the top line, you see the total of the contact’s invoices, the amount granted to your customer in form of credit notes and the difference between the two amounts. Orders and credit notes are listed as processes in the table. The <strong>Paid</strong> and <strong>Outstanding</strong> columns are especially helpful. If a payment for an order is listed in the <strong>Outstanding</strong> column, then the contact still has to pay the amount. As soon as this is done, the amount will be listed under <strong>Paid</strong>. If a payment for a credit note is listed in the <strong>Outstanding</strong> column, then you still have to pay this amount to the contact. As soon as this is done, the amount will be listed under <strong>Paid</strong>.</p>
</div>
