<h2 id="1890">12. Managing bank data</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the following sub-chapters, you will learn how to add new bank data for your contact as well as edit and delete existing bank data.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1900">12.1. Adding bank data</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Bank data</strong> view, you can add the bank data of your contact. You can add as many data records as you like.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After saving, the bank data will be displayed as cards. Beside the name of the holder and the IBAN, a tag will be displayed that shows whether the SEPA direct debit mandate is activated for the contact. If the BIC is saved in the bank data, this will also be shown on the card.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding bank data:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Bank data</strong> in the context menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>New bank data</strong> view will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-bank-data-contact">Table 9</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
