<h2 id="2200">13. Managing events</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the following sub-chapters, you will learn how to add, display and delete contact events. If you want your contact to pay for a certain event, it is also possible to bill those events.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2300">13.1. Adding an event</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Add as many contact events as you like. For example, the event can be a call or an email. You can enter a duration, select information about the process and enter a comment about the event into the text field. If you would like to bill the event, click on <strong>Add and bill</strong> when adding the event.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding an event:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Events</strong> in the context menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the type from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the duration of the event in minutes.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the info from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the info text.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add event</strong>.<br>
→ Select <strong>Add and bill</strong> or <strong>Add</strong>. The event will be added to the list.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2400">13.2. Displaying events</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can display the events that you have saved for your contacts at any time.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It is also possible to update the duration of the event directly in the overview. How to update the duration is described in the box at the end of this chapter.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Displaying events:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Events</strong> in the context menu.<br>
→ A list of the events will be displayed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Updating the duration of an event</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can update the duration of existing events. To do so, click on <strong>Update duration</strong> in the event overview. The window <strong>Update event duration</strong> will open. Enter the new number in minutes and click on <strong>Update</strong>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2500">13.3. Deleting an event</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Delete events that you no longer need.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting an event:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Events</strong> in the context menu.<br>
→ A list of the events will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong> in the line of the event that you want to delete.<br>
→ A window will open and you need to confirm your decision.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong>.<br>
→ The event will be deleted and removed from the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
